Sukumaran's mother Raji, brother Chintu and sister Brintha left the prison feeling distraught as they spoke with reporters waiting outside.

Mrs Sukumaran pleaded for President Joko Widodo to spare her son and Chan.

'Please don't kill them, they are good children,' she said.

Brintha cried as she begged for her older brother's life.

'Please don't kill my brother, please,' she said.

'He's rehabilitated and we love him so much.

'Please don't kill him, please. Please.'

